WEBVTT

00:07.008 --> 00:09.641
MAN (O.S): Atmospheric
compression.

00:11.412 --> 00:13.612
(Static)

00:18.185 --> 00:20.719
MAN (O.S): Discovery Houston,
you're a go at throttle up.

00:20.721 --> 00:22.588
MAN (O.S): Roger Houston,
going throttle up.

00:24.592 --> 00:28.527
Throttling back up
to 104 percent.

00:30.064 --> 00:34.733
All engines showing 104 percent
at this time.

00:40.708 --> 00:42.174
DOCTOR: So...

00:42.176 --> 00:43.575
Angus.

00:43.577 --> 00:47.079
New meds should help the
Transient Ischaemic Attacks.

00:47.081 --> 00:50.783
TIA, Atrial Fibrillation,
Angina.

00:50.785 --> 00:52.785
Well you know the score.

00:52.786 --> 00:54.786
Doctor Kumar is back next week
and I'll fill him in.

00:54.789 --> 00:55.788
Any more dizziness?

00:55.790 --> 00:58.090
Breathlessness, fainting?

00:58.793 --> 01:00.459
ANGUS: No.

01:00.461 --> 01:02.795
DOCTOR: No more driving.

01:02.797 --> 01:04.463
You live alone?

01:04.465 --> 01:07.166
ANGUS: Just moved in
with my daughter.

01:07.168 --> 01:08.801
DOCTOR: Excellent.

01:08.803 --> 01:10.469
Keep up the good fight, Angus.

01:10.471 --> 01:12.538
Because what's the alternative?

01:15.476 --> 01:18.077
(Whimsical Music)

02:33.187 --> 02:34.753
(Serene Music)

02:39.260 --> 02:40.659
ANGUS: Hey.

02:43.564 --> 02:46.465
How ya doing, Rosie?

02:51.572 --> 02:53.338
BARNEY: Granddad?

02:55.176 --> 02:57.026
Can I look?

02:57.027 --> 02:58.877
ANGUS: Yeah, as long as you stop
calling me granddad.

03:02.550 --> 03:04.283
BARNEY: Wow!

03:04.285 --> 03:05.584
Looks so close.

03:05.586 --> 03:06.919
ANGUS: Yeah.

03:06.921 --> 03:11.290
Like you can reach out
and touch it.

03:11.292 --> 03:15.394
People have been looking up
at the stars forever.

03:15.396 --> 03:18.297
And I think it's always
for the same reason.

03:18.299 --> 03:19.464
BARNEY: What?

03:19.466 --> 03:23.302
ANGUS: To see where we belong.

03:23.304 --> 03:25.504
That's a question I've been
asking myself

03:25.506 --> 03:27.639
my whole life.

03:30.377 --> 03:32.611
BARNEY: I wish I could be
an astronaut.

03:32.613 --> 03:34.846
ANGUS: You can.

03:34.848 --> 03:36.782
You can be anything you want.

03:36.784 --> 03:38.784
BARNEY: They only want
smart people.

03:38.786 --> 03:39.851
ANGUS: Well, you're smart.

03:39.853 --> 03:42.955
BARNEY: I got a D in math.

03:42.957 --> 03:47.359
ANGUS: Hey, I wasn't very
good at math myself.

03:52.499 --> 03:54.499
Rosie used to say,

03:54.501 --> 03:58.237
'on every special occasion,
you make a wish.'

03:58.872 --> 04:01.974
and that comet,

04:01.976 --> 04:04.409
that's a special occasion.

04:04.645 --> 04:06.945
BARNEY: Dad says wishes
don't come true.

04:09.283 --> 04:11.516
ANGUS: He does?

04:11.518 --> 04:12.918
Hmm.

04:21.528 --> 04:23.729
MOLLY: Finally got his telescope
out of the shed.

04:28.335 --> 04:30.269
JIM: That's good.

04:31.905 --> 04:33.672
MOLLY: Hey don't forget you have
homework tonight.

04:33.674 --> 04:35.290
Maybe Angus can help you out.

04:35.291 --> 04:36.907
BARNEY: Yeah, I'll finish it.
JIM: Wait, I can help him.

04:37.411 --> 04:39.678
MOLLY: Here, dad.

04:43.550 --> 04:45.684
JIM: Should you be drinking
that?

04:45.686 --> 04:47.286
Your heart.

04:47.287 --> 04:48.887
MOLLY: It's good for his heart,
enjoy dad!

04:48.889 --> 04:50.022
ANGUS: Thanks.

04:50.024 --> 04:51.390
BARNEY (O.S.): Angus!

04:51.392 --> 04:52.624
Come here!

04:53.827 --> 04:56.061
ANGUS: I've been summoned.

05:00.701 --> 05:02.034
BARNEY: It's him!

05:02.036 --> 05:03.702
TV VOICE (O.C.):
Tonight in our studio,

05:03.704 --> 05:06.405
We have the billionaire,
entrepreneur, Marcus Brown

05:06.407 --> 05:09.074
making a very special
announcement.

05:09.710 --> 05:11.844
JOURNALIST: Marcus.

05:11.845 --> 05:13.979
You've spoken about how your
father always supported

05:13.981 --> 05:16.048
your passion to go into space.

05:16.050 --> 05:18.350
MARCUS: Well, he always believed
everyone should have

05:18.352 --> 05:20.619
a chance to achieve
their dreams.

05:20.621 --> 05:22.054
JOURNALIST:
He died recently...

05:22.056 --> 05:24.890
MARCUS: And the Ventura
competition

05:24.892 --> 05:27.025
will honour his memory

05:27.027 --> 05:30.996
a lottery to choose someone who
dares to dream big.

05:30.998 --> 05:32.898
JOURNALIST: And the prize?

05:32.900 --> 05:34.533
MARCUS: A two-week journey
to space

05:34.535 --> 05:37.369
on the first commercial space
plane.

05:37.371 --> 05:40.505
We'll pull twelve names
from the lottery hat

05:40.507 --> 05:42.474
then the public votes
and for the winner.

05:42.476 --> 05:44.576
MARCUS: Who will join six other-
ANGUS: Turn it up!

05:45.446 --> 05:47.446
JOURNALIST: Are you ready?
MARCUS: We're ready.

05:47.448 --> 05:49.448
The competition is live now.

05:49.450 --> 05:52.617
So get your entry in before
midnight on Friday.

05:52.619 --> 05:54.986
Our March the 1st launch
is coming up fast.

05:54.988 --> 05:57.422
And I could be taking you.

05:58.759 --> 06:00.692
BARNEY: It's started!

06:03.097 --> 06:04.563
ANGUS: You know how many
runways there are

06:04.565 --> 06:06.365
that are that long in the whole
country?

06:06.367 --> 06:08.066
Maybe two or three.

06:08.068 --> 06:10.068
And they need that length
because

06:10.070 --> 06:12.104
this ship takes off like
an aeroplane

06:12.106 --> 06:14.806
and it's fuelled by
liquid hydrogen.

06:16.777 --> 06:19.511
Boy, they must have done some
serious reinforcement

06:19.513 --> 06:22.781
to that original runway.

06:22.783 --> 06:24.783
Got to have the right road.

06:24.785 --> 06:27.686
JOURNALIST: Some have said
you've taken risks

06:27.688 --> 06:30.555
in order to be the first
commercial space flight.

06:30.557 --> 06:32.991
MARCUS: Everything has an
element of risk.

06:32.993 --> 06:35.127
But, safety is our first
priority.

06:35.129 --> 06:36.895
Always.

06:38.665 --> 06:40.065
BARNEY: Angus, look that this.

06:40.067 --> 06:43.635
If you win, companies
pay you money.

06:43.837 --> 06:45.604
ANGUS: Look at that.

06:45.606 --> 06:49.441
Age requirement, eighteen
to sixty- five.

06:51.678 --> 06:53.578
BARNEY: You should sign up.

06:53.814 --> 06:55.647
ANGUS: Barney.

06:55.649 --> 06:56.815
It's a lottery.

06:56.817 --> 06:59.751
It's like winning a lottery.

06:59.753 --> 07:03.422
They need people who are fit
or in shape,

07:03.424 --> 07:04.956
you know, they don't want old.

07:07.060 --> 07:08.960
BARNEY: You could look
sixty-five.

07:14.101 --> 07:15.767
ANGUS: No, I couldn't.

07:26.613 --> 07:27.846
ENGINEER: Good night, Marcus.

07:27.848 --> 07:29.614
MARCUS: Have a good night.

07:36.056 --> 07:38.123
(Tranquil Music)

08:15.896 --> 08:17.596
ANGUS (O.S): You stay here.

08:17.898 --> 08:19.498
You wait for mommy.

08:20.501 --> 08:22.601
BARNEY: Angus, don't forget
about the competition.

08:24.071 --> 08:25.237
Bye mom!

08:25.239 --> 08:26.771
MOLLY: Hey, the tutor-

08:26.773 --> 08:28.907
the money for the tutor.
ANGUS: Hey.

08:28.909 --> 08:30.842
MOLLY: Got it, okay.

08:32.913 --> 08:34.646
Thanks, dad.

08:36.216 --> 08:40.185
ANGUS: What was the name
of that doll you had

08:40.187 --> 08:42.787
god, you carried it everywhere,
that mom bought you?

08:42.789 --> 08:43.788
MOLLY: Patty.

08:43.790 --> 08:45.257
ANGUS: Patty, right.

08:45.259 --> 08:48.126
Because you had to pat her
before she burped.

08:50.264 --> 08:52.564
MOLLY: Dad, the realtor thinks
that we should lower

08:52.566 --> 08:55.634
the price on the house.

08:55.636 --> 08:57.769
ANGUS: Maybe I won't sell her.

08:57.938 --> 08:59.704
MOLLY: It's just all the debt
Mom got into.

08:59.706 --> 09:01.139
ANGUS: Aw she didn't know what
she was doing

09:01.141 --> 09:03.275
when she did that, she was not
in the right mind.

09:03.277 --> 09:05.143
MOLLY: What kind of company
sells a donkey sanctuary

09:05.145 --> 09:06.745
to a seventy-five year
old woman,

09:06.747 --> 09:09.948
with dementia?
ANGUS: A criminal one.

09:09.950 --> 09:12.717
MOLLY: Dad, we should talk about
selling that too.

09:15.656 --> 09:17.856
ANGUS: You know um,

09:17.858 --> 09:20.725
I'm gonna take the dog
for a walk alone.

09:22.796 --> 09:25.864
MOLLY: Do you have your phone
on you?

09:25.866 --> 09:28.700
ANGUS: You know,
I can still walk.

09:32.606 --> 09:34.072
(Door Slams)

09:46.954 --> 09:48.720
ANGUS: Freeze thaw, huh?

09:51.124 --> 09:54.693
The subsurface may have
some limestone.

09:54.695 --> 09:58.296
That's what's causing
all the cavings.

09:58.298 --> 10:00.665
You know these roads were only
meant to last

10:00.667 --> 10:02.233
about twenty years.

10:03.303 --> 10:04.302
ROAD CONSTRUCTION WORKER: Yah.

10:04.304 --> 10:06.605
I'll keep that in mind.

10:13.647 --> 10:16.314
(River Flowing)

10:20.287 --> 10:23.088
(Kids Playing)

10:28.362 --> 10:30.629
(Mellow Music)

10:42.876 --> 10:44.943
(Radio Plays Funky Music)

11:01.728 --> 11:02.961
JIM: Molly.

11:03.296 --> 11:04.729
Molly.

11:05.732 --> 11:06.865
Molly.

11:08.268 --> 11:10.869
What the hell's he doing now?

11:15.676 --> 11:17.075
JIM: Angus.

11:18.045 --> 11:20.745
Angus, please.

11:20.747 --> 11:22.380
Some of us gotta work tomorrow.

11:22.382 --> 11:25.917
ANGUS: Yes, one minute.

11:25.919 --> 11:27.318
Thank you.

11:35.062 --> 11:37.128
(Coughing)

12:06.093 --> 12:08.159
(Wheezing)

12:10.030 --> 12:13.364
(Wheezing)

12:20.107 --> 12:22.273
MOLLY: Dad, are you ok?
ANGUS: Yeah.

12:22.275 --> 12:23.975
MOLLY: Do you need your spray?

12:23.977 --> 12:27.378
Okay, okay, deep breaths, daddy.

12:29.950 --> 12:32.016
Deep breaths.

12:43.463 --> 12:45.897
(Heavy Breathing)

12:56.243 --> 12:57.976
MOLLY: I got you, daddy.

13:06.153 --> 13:09.387
NURSE: Well, I look forward to
hearing from you.

13:09.389 --> 13:11.322
JIM: Thank you.
NURSE: Bye.

13:18.498 --> 13:20.498
JOE: You're lovely.

13:22.269 --> 13:24.435
NURSE: Dinner time, Joe.

13:27.440 --> 13:28.439
JIM (O.S.): Listen, your father,

13:28.441 --> 13:30.175
he can stay here if he wants

13:30.177 --> 13:32.177
but remember how sick you got
with your mother.

13:32.179 --> 13:34.312
You never slept, you were
always anxious,

13:34.314 --> 13:36.181
you gave up on your
teacher's degree,

13:36.183 --> 13:37.849
your father couldn't cope.

13:37.851 --> 13:40.185
You were left doing it all.

13:40.187 --> 13:42.070
I'm not having you go through
that again.

13:42.071 --> 13:43.954
MOLLY (O.S): You mean, you don't
want to go through that again.

13:43.957 --> 13:46.357
Don't you dare try to shove my
father into a home.

13:46.359 --> 13:48.026
JIM: I'm not trying to shove him
in a home,

13:48.028 --> 13:49.494
he's said he didn't want
to be a burden.

13:49.496 --> 13:51.529
MOLLY: He's not there yet,
not even close.

13:51.531 --> 13:53.898
And when the time comes, it will
be my decision.

13:53.900 --> 13:55.466
Not yours!

14:02.209 --> 14:04.609
(Mellow Guitar Music)

14:46.253 --> 14:47.652
MOLLY: Dad.

14:49.022 --> 14:50.421
Dad.

14:52.058 --> 14:53.791
Dad.

14:53.792 --> 14:55.525
BARNEY: He wouldn't be here
if it wasn't for you, dad.

14:55.528 --> 14:57.428
JIM: More complicated
than that Barn.

14:57.430 --> 14:59.063
MOLLY: He can always
come back home.

15:02.135 --> 15:03.968
ANGUS: Crappy stuff.

15:07.274 --> 15:09.908
LIZ: You must be Angus.
ANGUS: Yes.

15:09.910 --> 15:11.342
MOLLY: Thank you for getting us
in so fast.

15:11.344 --> 15:12.977
LIZ: Oh you're welcome.

15:12.979 --> 15:14.178
(Alarm Ringing)
LIZ: So, here are the forms

15:14.180 --> 15:15.413
to fill out.

15:15.415 --> 15:17.382
But, we'll see how we do.

15:17.384 --> 15:18.983
MOLLY: I think he just wants
to have a trial.

15:18.985 --> 15:20.919
LIZ: As you can hear,
new fire doors

15:20.921 --> 15:22.186
are being installed.

15:22.188 --> 15:25.056
We're working on the teething
problems.

15:25.058 --> 15:26.691
LIZ: Lunch-

15:28.061 --> 15:30.495
lunch is at noon, dinner at six.

15:30.497 --> 15:32.163
BARNEY: Doesn't get hungry
until eight.

15:32.165 --> 15:34.065
NURSE: Well, he will here.

15:34.067 --> 15:35.633
LIZ: This is a lovely room.

15:35.635 --> 15:38.202
Now, I am always in my office.

15:38.204 --> 15:41.072
So you can come and talk to me,
anytime.

15:45.312 --> 15:51.082
NURSE: Now, feel free to join in
for pat the dog and songs.

15:51.084 --> 15:53.017
MOLLY: He doesn't sing.

15:53.019 --> 15:55.653
NURSE: Right, okay.

15:55.655 --> 15:56.654
There's your bell.

15:56.656 --> 15:58.656
You can ring any time.

15:58.658 --> 16:01.492
And we will be right there,
right away.

16:08.702 --> 16:10.068
MOLLY: Okay Dad.

16:12.339 --> 16:14.172
Here's your phone, okay?

16:14.975 --> 16:16.708
I'm going to call you later.

16:24.050 --> 16:25.383
JIM: Have a good dinner.

16:27.687 --> 16:29.287
C'mon Barns.

16:34.361 --> 16:36.294
BARNEY: You shouldn't be here.

16:37.697 --> 16:40.131
(Fire Alarm)

16:54.147 --> 16:57.715
ELISA: Some questions to ask the
short listed contestants.

16:57.717 --> 16:59.650
MARCUS: 'Why do you want
to go to space?'

16:59.652 --> 17:00.718
Original question.

17:00.720 --> 17:02.086
(Chuckles)

17:02.088 --> 17:03.454
ELISA: I didn't write them.

17:04.657 --> 17:06.791
BILL: Hydrogen line is
still leaking.

17:08.261 --> 17:10.395
ELISA: We may have to push
the launch.

17:10.397 --> 17:11.696
MARCUS: They'll fix it.

17:11.698 --> 17:14.098
Nearly three hundred thousand
submissions.

17:14.100 --> 17:15.266
Twelve names.

17:15.268 --> 17:16.701
One ticket.

17:16.703 --> 17:18.536
Take off has to be a great show.

17:21.808 --> 17:23.208
RADIO VOICE (V.O.):
And finally,

17:23.209 --> 17:24.609
submissions for the Ventura
space competition

17:24.611 --> 17:27.378
close at midnight with already
thousands of applicants.

17:27.380 --> 17:29.264
Twelve of those names
will be drawn

17:29.265 --> 17:31.149
from the lottery hat, so could
one of them be you?

17:33.787 --> 17:35.386
NURSE: Nut cases.

17:35.388 --> 17:36.421
(Speaker Bell)

17:36.423 --> 17:37.755
NURSE: Breakfast.

17:37.757 --> 17:39.223
ANGUS: Um, I'm not-
I don't-

17:39.225 --> 17:41.292
NURSE: Yeah, yeah,
you will.

17:50.437 --> 17:52.737
ALICE: These eggs are rubbery.

17:54.374 --> 17:56.441
(Orchestral Background Music)

18:08.788 --> 18:12.457
JOE: I can leave this joint
anytime I want.

18:16.463 --> 18:18.796
SPEAKER: Don't forget ladies
and gentlemen

18:18.798 --> 18:22.400
the hairdresser will be in today
from 10 til 4.

18:33.179 --> 18:38.783
(Maggie Sings)

18:38.785 --> 18:44.489
¶ I ain't got nobody

18:44.491 --> 18:50.228
¶ And nobody cares for me

18:50.230 --> 18:52.897
JENNY: She's a little flat
don't you think?

18:55.535 --> 19:00.538
(Maggie Continues Singing)

19:01.141 --> 19:06.310
¶ I ain't got nobody

19:06.312 --> 19:09.747
¶ And nobody cares for-

19:09.749 --> 19:12.717
¶ Nobody cares for-

19:12.719 --> 19:16.854
¶ Nobody cares for me

19:16.856 --> 19:19.524
¶ Snowflake is nine,
aint that devine

19:19.526 --> 19:22.226
¶ Won't you be mine ¶

19:23.229 --> 19:24.795
MAGGIE: Thank you.

19:24.797 --> 19:26.564
(Applause)

19:28.601 --> 19:30.635
MAGGIE: And I'll see some of you
next week.

19:31.538 --> 19:33.304
(Phone Buzzes)

19:35.175 --> 19:36.407
(Angus Sighs)

19:39.212 --> 19:40.611
(Door Knocking)

19:44.250 --> 19:46.417
ALICE: Do you want to dance?

19:47.554 --> 19:49.320
(Chuckles)

19:52.859 --> 19:55.626
ALICE: It does get better
you know.

20:02.802 --> 20:05.303
(Tranquil Music)

20:21.588 --> 20:22.920
(Mumbles)

20:27.794 --> 20:30.528
NURSE: Right then Len, Angus.

20:30.530 --> 20:34.332
Time to come in.
ANGUS: Did you see the thing?

20:34.334 --> 20:37.602
NURSE: -in the pitch black,
guest residents inside now.

20:37.604 --> 20:40.504
ANGUS: I'll take care of him.
NURSE: I've got to close up.

20:42.775 --> 20:44.008
NURSE (O.S): Angus.

20:52.952 --> 20:54.986
ANGUS: Night.
LEN (Mumbles): Night.

20:56.422 --> 20:57.989
(Crying)

21:05.632 --> 21:08.566
NURSE: I know, I know.
(Alice Panting)

21:17.644 --> 21:19.710
(Serene Music)

21:59.686 --> 22:01.519
ANGUS: Do you suffer from
diabetes?

22:01.521 --> 22:02.553
Anxiety?

22:02.555 --> 22:04.655
Heart condition?

22:05.925 --> 22:07.992
No.

22:10.697 --> 22:13.998
P-E-R-F-E-C-T.

22:15.068 --> 22:17.835
ANGUS: Photo.

22:17.837 --> 22:20.571
Photo, photo, photo.

22:28.815 --> 22:30.047
Good.

22:35.588 --> 22:38.989
'Reasons why I should be
chosen.'

22:41.861 --> 22:43.994
(Typing)

22:50.737 --> 22:52.837
ANGUS: Ready to submit.

23:08.888 --> 23:11.589
(Garage Closing)

23:16.095 --> 23:18.028
(Mumbles)

23:20.767 --> 23:22.400
ANGUS: What?

23:24.771 --> 23:26.070
(Mumbles)

23:29.642 --> 23:31.542
(Mumbles)

23:34.113 --> 23:36.180
ANGUS: I don't understand.

23:38.117 --> 23:39.984
BARNEY: Angus!

23:39.985 --> 23:41.852
MOLLY: Sorry we're late dad,
I tried calling you.

23:41.854 --> 23:44.622
BARNEY: They made me stay back
for more stupid math.

23:44.624 --> 23:46.056
MOLLY: Yeah, well, you'll thank
me when you're older.

23:46.058 --> 23:47.691
BARNEY: Yeah, when I'm like
dead older.

23:48.127 --> 23:50.728
NURSE: Pardon me, Liz would
like a word.

23:50.730 --> 23:52.263
MOLLY: Okay.

23:52.264 --> 23:53.797
NURSE: Angus, are you settling
in nicely?

23:53.800 --> 23:56.401
ANGUS: Oh, uh,

23:56.402 --> 23:59.003
I really don't think I'm going
to be here for very long.

23:59.005 --> 24:00.905
NURSE: Nonsense.

24:00.907 --> 24:04.041
You are very robust.
MOLLY: Dad, I'll be right back.

24:04.043 --> 24:05.476
Barney.

24:10.583 --> 24:12.149
BARNEY: What?

24:12.151 --> 24:15.152
ANGUS: What, you're not even
going to guess?

24:15.154 --> 24:17.688
BARNEY: Guess what?

24:17.690 --> 24:20.558
ANGUS: Well you said
I could look 65.

24:23.830 --> 24:25.830
BARNEY: No no no,
no no no,

24:25.832 --> 24:27.164
You entered the competition?

24:27.166 --> 24:28.532
ANGUS: Yup!

24:28.534 --> 24:30.167
BARNEY: Oh my gosh,
yes yes yes!

24:30.636 --> 24:32.169
(Laughs)

24:35.641 --> 24:37.608
BARNEY: Does he know?

24:37.610 --> 24:39.610
ANGUS: His name is Len.

